org.tms.api

Interface IndexableTableElements

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    InitializableTableProperties, Table, TableContext

    public interface IndexableTableElements
    This interface defines the methods that are common to TableContext and Table instances that allow Row, Column, Cell, and Subset, labels to be indexed. When called on a TableContext, these methods establish the defaults that are used to construct new tables in that TableContext. When invoked on a specific Table, they affect that table immediately.

    When invoked on a specific Table, they get and set the values for that specific Table.

    Since:
    "1.0"
    Version:
    "1.0"

      • isRowLabelsIndexed

        Returns:
        true if the Row labels in this Table are indexed

      • setRowLabelsIndexed

        void setRowLabelsIndexed(boolean isIndexed)
        Set to true to index the Row labels in this Table. Indexed rows are faster to retrieve, which makes parsing Derivations more performant, and/but the labels must all be unique.
        Parameters:
        isIndexed - true or false
        Throws:
        NotUniqueException - if isIndexed is true and this table contains non-unique row labels
        DeletedElementException - if this table has been deleted
